  "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/zipball/v12.138.0",
  "body": "## What's Changed\r\n* feat: [SVLS-8493] rename durable function execution tags by @lym953 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/pull/748\r\n* fix: [SVLS-8538] apply durable function tags via setTag on the active span by @lym953 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/pull/762\r\n* feat: [SVLS-8721] add first_invocation tag for durable functions by @lym953 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/pull/761\r\n* [SVLS-8583] Add execution_status tag to aws.lambda span for durable functions by @lym953 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/pull/764\r\n* support us2 govcloud environment by @ojproductions in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/pull/765\r\n* [SVLS-8538] feat: rename durable function span tags to aws.durable.* by @lym953 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/pull/778\r\n* [SVLS-518] fix: fix broken SFN -> lambda link by @ida613 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/pull/779\r\n\r\n## New Contributors\r\n* @ida613 made their first contribution in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/pull/779\r\n\r\n**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/compare/v12.137.0...v12.138.0\r\n\r\n>[!IMPORTANT]\r\n> This version imports `dd-trace-js` [v5.93.0](https://github.com/DataDog/dd-trace-js/releases/tag/v5.93.0)\r\n\r\n\r\n```yml\r\n# AWS Commercial\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Node18-x:138\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Node20-x:138\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Node22-x:138\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Node24-x:138\r\n\r\n# AWS GovCloud\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Node18-x:138\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Node20-x:138\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Node22-x:138\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Node24-x:138\r\n\r\nACCOUNT =\r\n002406178527 for us1 environment\r\n486696501492 for us2 environment\r\n```",
